A-DO-CONHECIMENTO="CIENCIAS_EXATAS_E_DA_TERRA" NOME-DA-AREA-DO-CONHECIMENTO="Qumica" NOME-DA-SUB-AREA-DO-CONHECIMENTO="Fsico-Qumica" NOME-DA-ESPECIALIDADE="Eletroqumica"/><AREA-DO-CONHECIMENTO-2 NOME-GRANDE-AREA-DO-CONHECIMENTO="ENGENHARIAS" NOME-DA-AREA-DO-CONHECIMENTO="Engenharia Mecnica" NOME-DA-SUB-AREA-DO-CONHECIMENTO="Engenharia mecnica; Manuteno Industrial; Siderurgia; Corroso atmosfrica;" NOME-DA-ESPECIALIDADE=""/></AREAS-DO-CONHECIMENTO><SETORES-DE-ATIVIDADE SETOR-DE-ATIVIDADE-1="Manuteno, reparao e instalao de mquinas e equipamentos" SETOR-DE-ATIVIDADE-2="" SETOR-DE-ATIVIDADE-3=""/><INFORMACOES-ADICIONAIS DESCRICAO-INFORMACOES-ADICIONAIS="" DESCRICAO-INFORMACOES-ADICIONAIS-INGLES="This work aims the discussion on aspects of plant preservation and plant life extension&#10;program of a boiler installed in a siderurgic plant which has been in standby since 2009. The main&#10;objective is the preservation of all machinery, but special attention was delivered to the larger and&#10;most expansive equipment such as the boiler. Manufactures' instructions describe protective measures&#10;to preserve the inner walls of the pipework system from corrosion, but no attention is given to the&#10;external surface of all tubes inside the boiler, basically made of carbon steel. Moisture from natural&#10;condensation, pollutants such as chlorides and sulfur oxides from industrial atmosphere and&#10;temperature are important factors that should be controlled in order to avoid accelerated corrosion&#10;when the boiler isn't operating. Although chlorine and sulfur are known as catalysts for corrosion, it&#10;was found that the use of electrical resistances to heat the atmosphere inside the boiler to control&#10;temperature and humidity eludes condensation on the steel walls and is the main protective measure&#10;to avoid the deterioration of the equipment, reducing the corrosion rate from 0.139 mm/year to&#10;0.0431 mm/year.&#10;"/></TEXTO-EM-JORNAL-OU-REVISTA></TEXTOS-EM-JORNA